    {
      "id": "1924750c-f3ba-8083-9f1a-ef74a4ee0a40",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Authors propose a knowledge-aware recommendation that uses historical enrollments and learning feedback. The model uses a Knowledge graph to represent a learning sequence. The Learning sequence was combined with learning feedback to extract the students’ knowledge. Finally, an Attention module is used to predict the probability of enrolling in a course. Comparison with other baselines show that method can recommend MOOCs.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
